<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1406361683i/20738920._UX100_CR0,18,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/20738920-orinoco-womble-tidy-bag-and-all">Orinoco Womble (tidy bag and all)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">When you give a book a number of stars, a floating link appears that says &quot;Write a Review.&quot; For a book you&apos;ve already rated, hover your cursor in the <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">â€¦more</a></span><span class="fullContent">When you give a book a number of stars, a floating link appears that says "Write a Review." For a book you've already rated, hover your cursor in the area of the checkmark "Read" band, and the link will appear. Click on it, and it will take you to a window where you can write your review.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
